I&#8217;m a big fan of Microsoft&#8217;s &#8220;Natural Ergonomic Keyboard 4000&#8221;. I&#8217;m just not a fan of it&#8217;s name, it&#8217;s a mouthful! (How about for future reference we just call it the Ergo?)
&nbsp;
The Ergo&#8217;s great for typing on and also has a selection of feature keys that you can key-map to. Depending on your distro/desktop environment, you can map keys for all sorts of reasons: to replace caps lock with ctrl, control your music player, to run scripts, etc.

I keep a lot of notes&hellip;
Writing notes Any time I&rsquo;m researching anything computing related, whether it&rsquo;s for work or in my spare time, I keep a log of my &ldquo;stream of conciousness&rdquo;. This includes thoughts like &ldquo;I think this is because&hellip;&rdquo;, &ldquo;I wonder if this is related to&hellip;&rdquo;, &ldquo;What the fuck is&hellip;?&rdquo;.
This is great when I&rsquo;ve spent a lot of time learning something new and I can look back over them once a week to reinforce the stuff I&rsquo;ve covered.
